@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Bipaire" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Playing Bipaire is very simple, click on a tile and then click
on another tile that is like the first tile you clicked on. If the
tiles matches, they will be removed from the board, this can
reveal part of tiles that are located under.

  As the tiles are 'piled' up to 5 tiles high, the tiles located
under can't be seen unless the upper ones are removed. To help you
to see how many tiles there are on a game board, the number of
remaining tiles is displayed at the right.

  The game ends if you can't make any pairs with the remaining
tiles.

  When you remove the last pair on the game board, it is then
cleared and the game displays a new board that you have to clear
and so on up to the last board.

  You can restart a game by clicking on the @{b}Restart game@{ub} button,
but beware! This option restarts the game at the first board...

  Have fun!

